<span id="freeTextContainer8595054569910239636">This is set in Japan after the bombing of Hiroshima. We meet this athletic girl who loves to run who slowly can&apos;t run. She starts feeling pain and tiredness. It&apos;s discovered that she has leukemia and that was an after effect of the bomb and many people, including children 10 years after were experiencing. <br/><br/>Sadako hears the story of the child who makes a 1,000 paper cranes will have a wish come true. She decides to make 1000 cranes to heal herself. <br/><br/>This story doesn&apos;t have a happy ending. It&apos;s a go</span>
  <span id="freeText8595054569910239636" style="display:none">This is set in Japan after the bombing of Hiroshima. We meet this athletic girl who loves to run who slowly can't run. She starts feeling pain and tiredness. It's discovered that she has leukemia and that was an after effect of the bomb and many people, including children 10 years after were experiencing. <br /><br />Sadako hears the story of the child who makes a 1,000 paper cranes will have a wish come true. She decides to make 1000 cranes to heal herself. <br /><br />This story doesn't have a happy ending. It's a good little story for young readers and it explores a period in history we don't hear too much about. The epilogue is nice and there is a statue to this girl in Japan that people leave thousands of cranes for. <br /><br /></span>
